      <biogHist id="md5-f96075c443e9c99ba781b8ab7f3dfdd2">
        <p>In 1948, the Government of Alberta's Department of Economic Affairs created a Film and  Photography Branch, the purpose of which was to maintain a photographic record of Alberta's  economic, cultural and social development. In 1959, the Branch was transferred to the Provincial  Secretary and, after several more transfers, was taken under the Bureau of Public Affairs.</p>
